  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 6, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet to let it air</p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick with a matching lid) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your<strong> free range</strong> <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3 min on each side or until browned</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693819724648-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693819724648-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693819724648-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693819724648-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1693819724648-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the chicken has browned, add your <strong>ground cumin</strong>,<strong> dried oregano </strong>and a couple splashes of<strong> cold water</strong> to the pan and cook, covered, for a further 12-15 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your<strong> red onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Once the chicken is cooked through, transfer to a clean board and shred it apart, using two forks (reserve the pan)</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693819727417-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693819727417-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693819727417-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693819727417-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1693819727417-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a medium heat and add 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Once the butter has melted, add the <strong>sliced onion</strong> and<strong> chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until softened</p><p>Once softened, add 15g <span class=\"text-purple\">[20g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [30g]</span><strong> flour</strong> and your <strong>cayenne pepper</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and stir with a wooden spoon for 3-4 min or until a paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693819730420-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693819730420-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693819730420-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693819730420-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1693819730420-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>tomato paste</strong>, <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!)</p><p>Gradually whisk in 400ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[520ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [700ml] </span><strong>boiled</strong><span class=\"text-danger\"> </span><strong>water</strong>, a little at a time, and cook for 5 min (stirring occasionally) or until a smooth, thick sauce remains – this is your <strong>chipotle sauce</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, drain and rinse your <strong>black beans</strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1693819769709-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1693819769709-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1693819769709-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1693819769709-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1693819769709-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Remove 1/3 of the <strong>chipotle sauce</strong> to a small pot – this is your<strong> enchilada topping</strong></p><p>Add the<strong> drained black beans</strong> and <strong>pulled chicken</strong> to the <strong>remaining chipotle sauce</strong> in the pan and give it a good mix up – this is your <strong>chicken & black bean filling</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1693819772687-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1693819772687-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1693819772687-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1693819772687-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
